tip.text: Ask the guy to twirl your order of Roti Terbang (known as Roti Prata in Singapore) and watch as he makes it spin. I have never seen anyone do this anywhere else with this level of skill.
This food stall is right beside the main road that goes into Malacca old town. Look out for it and park by the side of the road on the dirt patch. Order the roti terbang and ask the guy to twirl it!
You have to try the tiny Banh Mi crunchy slices that they sell in small gift bags! They are addictive and perfect as a snack!
